author: @aKelev3n
text: Hi Alex, First of all, thanks for your content. Your videos are very informative and helpful for my research to becoming a data analyst. I am currently an accountant and have recently started looking at becoming an analyst. I did not have a computer science or statistics, or programming background but I know my excel and small amounts of SQL and your videos have encouraged me to start the transition.    I'm currently using Khan Academy for basic SQL, Stat, and looking at Coursera or Udemy for SQL and Python. I am also considering starting my road to get a certificate in Big Data from my local respected community college in my area. I was wondering if you could put out a video about which resources you used when you were self-teaching yourself some of the technical skills. I've also found that not a ton of jobs respect many of these boot camps that are popping up left and right, any opinion on that? Because bootcamps are over promising obviously to learning many items in just 12 weeks.  Again, thanks for the great honest and informative content and you're very encouraging on the career path switch. -AD
